{"author":{"id":"e60fd24f21ee24b4c65a7ef88cf96cfdf035b03f57c0cec80b97c5092f8433a3"},"ops":[{"type":6,"timestamp":1726275703,"nonce":"BTT7Gt6FhRTGZ4RJYQfhaNtZpRs=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lAHOCGKeh86WjkTdzmSwPFw"},"target":"eda813d503633f3af5ffa7fbdf0dac325febbcae133b6ff32fc97546aba44aed","message":"I created a bridge to a gitlab repo and configured it.\n\nHowever when I try to `git bug bridge pull` I got `Error: missing identity token` so I figured I did something wrong (what is an identity token? I provided an access token when I configured the bridge).\n\n`git bug bridge auth` shows the bridge:\n```\n909c824 gitlab     token \u003credacted\u003e base-url:https://gitlab.com/,login:project_61675907_bot_da4fbf9716170e7b652e0921346b75dd\n```\nOk I don't know what 'login:project_61675907_bot_da4fbf9716170e7b652e0921346b75dd` is, but I'll try to remove the bridge:\n```\n$ git bug bridge rm 909c824\nError: invalid key prefix\n```\nDoesn't work, neither does:\n```\n$ git bug bridge rm gitlab\nError: invalid key prefix\n```","files":null},{"type":6,"timestamp":1726275912,"nonce":"iWOVwMSTCgI4dTMSSQZPAc2e6ng=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lAHOCGKeh86WjkTdzmSwQrs"},"target":"eda813d503633f3af5ffa7fbdf0dac325febbcae133b6ff32fc97546aba44aed","message":"I created a bridge to a gitlab repo and configured it.\n\nHowever when I try to `git bug bridge pull` I got `Error: missing identity token` so I figured I did something wrong (what is an identity token? I provided an access token when I configured the bridge).\n\n`git bug bridge auth` shows the bridge:\n```\n909c824 gitlab     token \u003credacted\u003e base-url:https://gitlab.com/,login:project_61675907_bot_da4fbf9716170e7b652e0921346b75dd\n```\nOk I don't know what 'login:project_61675907_bot_da4fbf9716170e7b652e0921346b75dd` is, but I'll try to remove the bridge:\n```\n$ git bug bridge rm 909c824\nError: invalid key prefix\n```\nDoesn't work, neither does:\n```\n$ git bug bridge rm gitlab\nError: invalid key prefix\n```\n\nEdit:\nI also don't know how to manually delete the bridge, I tried removing the `.git/git-bug` directory, but `git bug bridge auth` still shows the bridge.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1726276944,"nonce":"RYIqRxYmajyktapzxsCZ6Vl8I/E=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOCGKeh86MHc8Z","github-url":"https://github.com/git-bug/git-bug/issues/1268#issuecomment-2350763801"},"message":"So I managed to reset the bridge configuration by removing the `~/.config/git-bug` directory.\n\nI also figured out that to remove the bridge, you need to use it's \"name\" (which was \"default\"), but this name isn't shown when you list the bridge with `git bug bridge auth`.\n\nAlso the original problem of getting 'Error: missing identity token' when trying to bridge pull seems to have been cause by using a *project access token*. Configuring the bridge using a *personal access token* allowed me to pull the issues. (Which by the way, the git bug dialog points to https://gitlab.com/-/profile/personal_access_tokens to create an access token, but this URL is no longer valid, it should be https://gitlab.com/-/user_settings/personal_access_tokens)","files":null},{"type":6,"timestamp":1726276977,"nonce":"w+4CbcudkiKS4Bi0zbBD2FpHyJA=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lALOCGKeh86MHc8Zzk-46gw"},"target":"a20798ec7edaaef9e592387294a01b9792d04d8281451f2ebf4927b4447d5802","message":"So I managed to reset the bridge configuration by removing the `~/.config/git-bug` directory.\n\nI also figured out that to remove the bridge, you need to use it's \"name\" (which was \"default\"), but this name isn't shown when you list the bridge with `git bug bridge auth`.\n\nAlso the original problem of getting 'Error: missing identity token' when trying to bridge pull seems to have been caused by using a *project access token*. Configuring the bridge using a *personal access token* allowed me to pull the issues. (Which by the way, the git bug dialog points to https://gitlab.com/-/profile/personal_access_tokens to 